[assistant] 抽取并记录信息: {"user_identity": "", "user_preference": "", "research_direction": "Randomised controlled trials and quasi‐randomised trials of conservative management to prevent or treat UI after TURP or radical prostatectomy were included. Trials were included if they used any single conservative therapy or any combination of conservative therapies. Other forms of clinical trials were excluded.", "filter_requirements": "Trials were included if they used any single conservative therapy or any combination of conservative therapies. Other forms of clinical trials were excluded. Analysis of trials in men having radical prostatectomy was done separately from those in men having a TURP. Adult men with UI following prostatectomy. PFMT; biofeedback (verbal or machine‐mediated); electrical stimulation (ES) via a surface electrode (e.g. anal probe ES, sticky patch electrode, transcutaneous electrical nerve stimulation (TENS)); extra‐corporeal magnetic innervation (ExMI); lifestyle adjustment; and external penile compression devices.", "rejection_reasons": "", "other_info": "This systematic review evaluates the effectiveness of various conservative treatments for post-prostatectomy urinary incontinence, including biofeedback, electrical stimulation, and external penile compression devices. The study focuses on randomised controlled trials comparing different interventions such as physical therapy (PFMT), biofeedback, electric or magnetic energy, lifestyle adjustments, and external penile compression devices. The outcomes measured include the number of men reporting urinary incontinence after 12 months, quality of life assessed using the ICIQ‐UI‐SF, adverse effects, cost-effective analysis, and other relevant metrics."}
